Subject: [PATCH] ppu/include/_ansi.h: restore _DEFUN/_AND/_NOARGS/_VOID

PSL1GHT's librt uses the K&R-vs-ANSI compatibility macros _DEFUN,
_AND, _NOARGS, and _VOID in 25+ source files.  Those macros lived
in newlib's <_ansi.h> through newlib 3.x; newlib 4.x dropped them
because the K&R compiler path is dead.  Modernizing every librt
file would be the long-term answer, but it is out of scope for
toolchain alignment and would churn a codebase that already has a
pending v3 naming RFC on top.

Interpose a one-screen <_ansi.h> ahead of newlib's copy: it
#include_next's newlib's real header (so _ATTRIBUTE, _BEGIN_STD_C,
_ELIDABLE_INLINE etc. are unchanged) and then defines the missing
macros back with their historical ANSI-mode expansions.  Only
PSL1GHT code that uses these macros sees any difference; newlib
itself and other consumers are unaffected.

These macros are not part of the reference cell SDK header set either — the
reference headers use plain ANSI prototypes — so nothing we add here conflicts with
matching the cell-SDK ABI.  The shim exists purely to let PSL1GHT's
existing librt sources continue to compile without a bulk rewrite.

diff --git a/ppu/include/_ansi.h b/ppu/include/_ansi.h
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..f4c1880
--- /dev/null
+++ b/ppu/include/_ansi.h
@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@
+/*
+ * PSL1GHT <_ansi.h> compat shim.
+ *
+ * Pulls newlib's real <_ansi.h> via #include_next, then re-adds the
+ * K&R-vs-ANSI compatibility macros (_DEFUN, _AND, _NOARGS, _VOID)
+ * that newlib 4.x dropped.  PSL1GHT's librt sources still use them.
+ *
+ * Placed in ppu/include so the PPU include path finds it before
+ * newlib's copy; #include_next then reaches newlib's real header.
+ */
+#ifndef _PSL1GHT_ANSI_COMPAT_H_
+#define _PSL1GHT_ANSI_COMPAT_H_
+
+#include_next <_ansi.h>
+
+#ifndef _DEFUN
+# define _DEFUN(name, args, parms) name(parms)
+# define _AND   ,
+# define _NOARGS void
+#endif
+
+#ifndef _VOID
+# define _VOID void
+#endif
+
+#endif /* _PSL1GHT_ANSI_COMPAT_H_ */
